`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The `seasonTint` is stored on the ECS `TreeComponent` (set by a seasonal system), then passed as a prop to `TreeModel` — this keeps the rendering component "dumb" (pure visual, no season logic)
- For GLB color tinting, we must clone materials after `scene.clone(true)` because Three.js deep-clone shares material references; without cloning, we'd mutate the useGLTF cache
- Species config drives `useWinterModel` (architectural decision: config is source of truth, not runtime ECS state)
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

